textMap.PRIMARY: Bonus Content: This episode of "The Man In the High Castle" is one of a number of titles that benefit from exclusive videos and behind-the-scenes photos, accessible in the X-Ray Bonus tab in Prime Video.
Neutral Zones in MITHC can be defined as unoccupied, de-militarized zones.

Under a mutual treaty, neither the Nazis nor the Japanese are allowed to exert authority in the Neutral Zone, which has allowed the territory to become a refuge for subversives, the disabled, the sexually and racially persecuted and people seeking some kind of freedom of expression or worship.

The Joe Blake we see in Season 3 is much closer to the Joe viewers may know from Philip K. Dick's novel. In the book, Joe, who had been posing as a truck driver, was revealed to be a Swiss assassin working for the SS.
Tagomi has consulted the I Ching throughout his life. The I Ching is an ancient Chinese text that is used as an oracle.

The art department spent a lot of time developing the sunrise artwork that pops up all across the JPS. Several iterations of the design were drafted on the way to the final icon of the new resistance.

The population of the Neutral Zone consists of a large percentage of African Americans, disabled, gay, Slavic and Jewish people as well as communists, Christians, intellectuals, artists and musicians.

In the alternative history of "The Man in the High Castle" the value of the Yen is roughly equivalent to the German Pfennig (i.e. 1/100th of a Deutschmark), this is demonstrated in the scene where a character pay 25 Yen for a glass of beer for example.
John Wayne, an icon of Hollywood westerns, was well known the Japanese who were fascinated by classic Americana. The last and most famous film he made in the alt-timeline was "Stagecoach" in 1939.
As a young filmmaker, Nicole is inspired by the work of Leni Riefensthal.

The monk self-immolation scene in Episode 304 draws inspiration from the life and death of Vietnamese Mahayana Buddhist monk Lm Van Tc who burned himself alive in the middle of a street in Saigon in 1963, in protest of the government's persecution of Buddhists.
Over the years, Nicole has had relationships with both women and men, daring to free herself from the conventional norms of her upbringing that feel old-fashioned and stifling.

Nazi Fascism is most potent when it is able to control minds remotely and encourage its subjects to self-police. Thomas Smith's decision to turn himself over to the state to be euthanized is a prime example of the power of Nazi ideological indoctrination.
The world's Neutral Zones in the MITHC alt history include the Rocky Mountain States in North America and Amazonia in South America.

Actor Jason O'Mara, who was born in Dublin, made an impression on the creative team during the casting process which led writers to reshape the backstory of the character Wyatt Price, making him an Irish-born fixer in Season 3.
